{"parentUuid":"3a53d701-e4fa-403e-9f06-bcaaa311a15e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a3b5a07652fc84308","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccs1JLMhx1Lt3h5uRkrLP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reconciliation passes (`reconciled: true`, no count mismatches, no scope gaps; `scan_reconciled: true`). Self-audit complete — all counts consistent across both artifacts, every finding inventoried, every STRIDE mechanism verified, ASVS reconciled.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Security scan of `feature/usage-export` (GET /v1/usage/export) — verdict: clean.**\n\nTools: Semgrep (auto + p/secrets + p/owasp-top-ten + p/python), OSV, Gitleaks, ASVS Tier-1 SAST, lockfile check, SBOM. Scope: diff (11 code-shaped changed files) vs `43da320`. Found 5 / fixed 0 / **0 critical remaining** → status `clean`, `scan_reconciled: true`.\n\n**Findings (all non-blocking):**\n- **2 Semgrep ERROR** (`avoid-sqlalchemy-text`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py:129,161`) — **verified false positives**. The `text()` f-strings interpolate only `where_clause`, which `_export_filter_clause_and_params` builds from fixed string literals; every filter value is a bound parameter and the `ORDER BY` is a fixed literal. No injection vector. Reported-only, excluded from `critical_count`.\n- **1 OSV CVE** — `pytest==8.3.4` (`PYSEC-2026-1845`/`GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g`, tmpdir handling, CVSS ~6.8 Moderate, dev-only). Below the 7.0 gate floor; safe upgrade is **pytest → 9.0.3** (Action required, not auto-fixed).\n- **125 Gitleaks hits** — all `.venv/` dependency example data or test-fixture false positives; no committed secret in the change set.\n- **RLS `FORCE` inert on `usage_rollup`** — pre-existing accepted risk (plan R2/Open Q3); tenant isolation relies on the effective explicit `api_key_id` predicate, not the inert backstop. Not worsened by this feature.\n\n**Verified effective (not just present):** IDOR/BOLA closed via mandatory `api_key_id`-first predicate on both new queries; Pydantic allowlist validation + `extra=\"forbid\"`; CSV formula-injection escape at the sink; identity-keyed Tier-2 throttle (no ALB single-bucket pitfall); async-only DB calls (no event-loop stall); no PII/secrets in logs (booleans, not values). All 8 STRIDE mechanisms verified; ASVS V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V13/V14/V16 reconciled at L1+L2; input-surface and data-surface reconciled.\n\n**Disclosed skip:** ast-grep is not installed on PATH (wrapper exit 2) — the two syntax-shaped concerns it would flag (f-string SQL, KDF-on-event-loop) were verified manually instead. Advisory-only, no gate impact.\n\nArtifacts:\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-report.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-status.json`\n- Raw scans: `.pipeline\\semgrep.json`, `.pipeline\\osv.json`, `.pipeline\\gitleaks.json`, `.pipeline\\asvs-sast.json`, `.pipeline\\sbom.cdx.json`, `.pipeline\\scan-reconciliation.json`"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":585,"cache_creation_input_tokens":628,"cache_read_input_tokens":106830,"output_tokens":1722,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":628},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":585,"output_tokens":1722,"cache_read_input_tokens":106830,"cache_creation_input_tokens":628,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":628,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs1JK6oT6adusqT5wdt6","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"65969c30-6822-48d2-a18d-34436ff15b8e","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:06:02.635Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec